│ My previous fix for the `nsw` miscompilation has caused a new regression, an assertion failure in a different test case      │
│ involving `nuw` and `trunc`. The crash occurs in `APInt::zext` but is triggered by a recursive call within                   │
│ `ConstantOffsetExtractor::find` that involves a `trunc` instruction.                                                         │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The backtrace indicates that the `find` function is called with `ZeroExtended=true`, and this flag is propagated down the    │
│ recursive calls. When `find` encounters a `TruncInst`, it recursively calls itself on the `TruncInst`'s operand. The problem │
│ is that `ZeroExtended` is a property that applies to the *result* of an operation, not its operands. A `trunc` operation can │
│ change the value in a way that makes the `ZeroExtended` assumption invalid for its operand.                                  │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ Specifically, if we have `zext(trunc(X))`, it is not equivalent to `trunc(zext(X))`. The `ZeroExtended` flag should not be   │
│ propagated through a `TruncInst`.                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ To fix this, I will modify the `find` function. In the `else if` block that handles `TruncInst`, I will change the recursive │
│ call to `find` to pass `false` for the `ZeroExtended` parameter. This will prevent the incorrect assumption from being       │
│ propagated and should fix the assertion failure.                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ I will use `sed` to replace the line containing the recursive call with a corrected version.                                 │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                      │
│ sed -i "s/find(U->getOperand(0), SignExtended, ZeroExtended, NonNegative)/find(U->getOperand(0), SignExtended, \/*           │
│ ZeroExtended *\/ false, NonNegative)/" llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/SeparateConstOffsetFromGEP.cpp                             │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
